  <h2 id="what-was-omegle">What Was Omegle?</h2>
  <p>Omegle was a free online chat platform launched in <strong>March 2009</strong> by Leif K-Brooks, who was just 18 years old at the time. It had a brilliantly simple concept — connect two random strangers anonymously for a one-on-one text or video conversation. No registration, no profiles, just pure random chat.</p>
  <p>For over a decade, Omegle became one of the most visited websites on the internet. At its peak, it was connecting millions of people every single day across the globe — from teenagers wanting to make friends to adults wanting to practice languages to researchers studying human connection.</p>

