  <h2 id="omegle-history">Omegle's Rise and Fall — A Timeline</h2>

  <div class="timeline fade-in">
    <div class="timeline-item">
      <div class="tl-date">March 2009</div>
      <h4>Omegle Launches</h4>
      <p>18-year-old Leif K-Brooks launches Omegle as a text-only random chat platform. It goes viral almost instantly, driven by word of mouth and social media.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="timeline-item">
      <div class="tl-date">2010</div>
      <h4>Video Chat Added</h4>
      <p>Omegle introduces video chat — a massive upgrade that sends traffic soaring. Millions of new users join to experience face-to-face random conversations.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="timeline-item">
      <div class="tl-date">2013</div>
      <h4>Interest Tags Introduced</h4>
      <p>Users can now enter interest tags to be matched with people who share similar hobbies. This feature dramatically improves conversation quality.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="timeline-item">
      <div class="tl-date">2020</div>
      <h4>COVID-19 Causes Traffic Explosion</h4>
      <p>During lockdowns, Omegle sees a massive surge in users seeking connection. Traffic reportedly increases by over 500% as people turn to random chat to fight loneliness.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="timeline-item">
